summ:
In response to the ESC's request made at the meeting held on 28.5.03, the Administration provided an information paper which detailed the creation and deletion of directorate posts after Implementation of the accountability system  [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/ei03-02e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>]
<br /><br />ESC endorsed the proposal to -
<table>
<tr><td valign="top"><small>&bull;</small>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top">create of one permanent post of Administrative Officer Staff Grade C (AOSGC) (D2)/non-civil service position at D2-equivalent in the Treasury Branch of Financial Services and the Treasury Bureau of Government Secretariat with effect from 1.7.03 as Administrative Assistant (AA) to Secretary for Financial Services and the Treasury, to be offset by deletion of one permanent post of Principal Valuation Surveyor (D1) in Rating and Valuation Department  [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/e03-09e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>];
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><small>&bull;</small>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top">create one permanent post of AOSGC (D2)/non-civil service position at D2-equivalent in the Home Affairs Bureau of Government Secretariat with effect from 1.7.03 as AA to Secretary for Home Affairs, to be offset by deletion of one permanent post of AOSGC (D2); deletion of one permanent post of AOSGC (D2); and redistribution the duties and responsibilities among the directorate posts on the establishment of the Bureau and the Home Affairs Department [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/e03-05e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>];
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><small>&bull;</small>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top">merge the Labour Branch of Economic Development and Labour Bureau of the Government Secretariat and the Labour Department; and creation of one permanent post of AOSGC (D2)/non-civil service position at D2-equivalent as AA to the Secretary for Economic Development and Labour with effect from 1.7.03  [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/e03-07e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>];
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><small>&bull;</small>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top">create one permanent post of AOSGC (D2)/non-civil service position at D2-equivalent as Principal Assistant Secretary cum AA to Secretary for Constitutional Affairs with effect from 1.7.03, to be offset by deletion of one permanent post of AOSGC (D2) in the Constitutional Affairs Bureau of the Government Secretariat [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/e03-08e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>];
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><small>&bull;</small>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top">create two permanent posts of one Administrative Officer Staff Grade A1 (D8) and one AOSGC (D2)/non-civil service position at D2-equivalent in the Health, Welfare and Food Bureau of Government Secretariat with effect from 1.7.03, to be offset by deletion of two permanent posts of one Administrative Officer Staff Grade A1 (D8) and one AOSGC (D2); and re-distribution of duties among the directorate posts in the Food and Environmental Hygiene Division of the Bureau [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/e03-11e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>]; and
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><small>&bull;</small>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top">create one permanent post of Administrative Officer Staff Grade A1 (D8) with effect from 1 July 2003; creation of one permanent post of Administrative Officer Staff Grade B (D3) with immediate effect and deletion of two permanent posts of Administrative Officer Staff Grade A1 (D8) with effect from 1.7.03 in the Environment and Transport Branch of Environment, Transport and Works Bureau of Government Secretariat; and deletion of one permanent post of Principal Executive Officer (D1) with effect from 1.11.03 in the Works Branch of the Bureau. [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/e03-06e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>]
</td></tr></table><br />
The LegCo Secretariat prepared a background brief for ESC on staffing proposals relating to the implementation of the accountability system for principal officials.  [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/esc47e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>]
<br /><br />At ESC's request, the Administration provided members with information on civil service directorate posts created for special purposes in organizations other than Government bureaux and departments, and which had been left vacant.  [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/esc-51-e-scan.pdf" target="_blank">Follow-up paper</a>]

In response to the ESC's request made at the meeting held on 28.5.03, the Administration provided an information paper which detailed the creation and deletion of directorate posts after Implementation of the accountability system  [<a href="http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr02-03/english/fc/esc/papers/ei03-02e.pdf" target="_blank">Paper</a>]
